</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Kyoto" /><category term="Shrines" /><category term="Foliage" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[A bright red maple tree along the path to the entrance of Kamigamo Jinja shrine. The flags are promoting Shichi-Go-San, a shrine festival for 7, 5, and 3 year olds. 上賀茂神社の参道沿いの真っ赤なモミジ。七五三の旗が立っている。]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2511_A7R00838_x.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2511_A7R00838_x.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Hojo at Myoken-ji・妙顕寺の方丈</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/251118/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Hojo at Myoken-ji・妙顕寺の方丈" /><published>2025-11-18T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2025-11-18T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/myokenji</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/251118/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
The sunlight after a rain is always beautiful. At Myokenji Temple.
</p>
<p class="jp">
雨上がりの日差しはいつも美しい。妙顕寺にて。

</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Kyoto" /><category term="Temples" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[The sunlight after a rain is always beautiful. At Myokenji Temple. 雨上がりの日差しはいつも美しい。妙顕寺にて。]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2511_IMG_2595.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2511_IMG_2595.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Red Leaves・かえで</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/251117/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Red Leaves・かえで" /><published>2025-11-17T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2025-11-17T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/rimlight</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/251117/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
 I love shooting maple leaves lit from behind, which makes them glow like stained glass. They are highlighted by the morning sunlight filtering through the trees.
</p>
<p class="jp">
カエデの葉を後ろから照らすと、ステンドグラスのように輝いて見える。木漏れ日が葉を際立たせている。

</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Kyoto" /><category term="Shrines" /><category term="Foliage" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[I love shooting maple leaves lit from behind, which makes them glow like stained glass. They are highlighted by the morning sunlight filtering through the trees. カエデの葉を後ろから照らすと、ステンドグラスのように輝いて見える。木漏れ日が葉を際立たせている。]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2511_DSC_1525_x.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2511_DSC_1525_x.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Nison-in・二尊院</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/251116/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Nison-in・二尊院" /><published>2025-11-16T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2025-11-16T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/nison-in</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/251116/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
Golden maple leaves in the morning sun, in the main temple grounds.
</p>
<p class="jp">
朝日に照らされた金色のもみじ。
</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Arashiyama" /><category term="Temples" /><category term="Foliage" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Golden maple leaves in the morning sun, in the main temple grounds. 朝日に照らされた金色のもみじ。]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2511_A7R00769_x-2.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2511_A7R00769_x-2.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Hogon-in・宝厳院</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/251115/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Hogon-in・宝厳院" /><published>2025-11-15T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2025-11-15T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/hogonin</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/251115/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
A sunny morning. An oasis of peace and tranquillity, steps away from the crowds. At the garden of Hogon-in Temple, a sub-temple of Tenryu-ji.
</p>
<p class="jp">
晴れた朝。人混みから少し離れた、静寂と安らぎのオアシス。天龍寺の塔頭、宝厳院の庭園にて。
</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Arashiyama" /><category term="Tenryu-ji" /><category term="Foliage" /><category term="Gardens" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[A sunny morning. An oasis of peace and tranquillity, steps away from the crowds. At the garden of Hogon-in Temple, a sub-temple of Tenryu-ji. 晴れた朝。人混みから少し離れた、静寂と安らぎのオアシス。天龍寺の塔頭、宝厳院の庭園にて。]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2511_A7R00686_x-2.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2511_A7R00686_x-2.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Observation Deck・展望台</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/251114/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Observation Deck・展望台" /><published>2025-11-14T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2025-11-14T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/tenbodai</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/251114/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
